Each of the thirty-four offenses has a fine or prison for a year and a half to a maximum of four years. But the age of the condemned, 77, and the lack of previous convictions exclude the possibility of a long detention and perhaps even a very short.&nbsp; The crime of falsification of documents to cover a scandal is considered of category E, the lowest in the scale of values of the State of New York. And it's non-violent crimes. But to be evaluated there will also be the continuous violations of the defendant to the prohibition of publicly accusing judges, prosecutors, jurors and witnesses. The sentence could be a fine, probation or, as a last hypothesis, prison. Trump may be forced to present himself in front of the criminal supervisor who will verify his behavior during the alternative prison period. It means complying with hours and days when you have to show up in person. The violation of "probation" includes severe penalties, including prison.
